  "cues": [
    {
      "index": "1",
      "start": "00:00:00,031",
      "end": "00:00:14,090",
      "text": "In 1912, fragments from a gravel pit in Sussex seemed to give British science the fossil it wanted, a human-like skull, an ape-like jaw, a famous name Piltdown Man."
    },
    {
      "index": "2",
      "start": "00:00:15,201",
      "end": "00:00:18,085",
      "text": "The evidence was thin, but the story was powerful."
    },
    {
      "index": "3",
      "start": "00:00:19,167",
      "end": "00:00:23,594",
      "text": "It fit a brain-first theory and gave Britain its own ancient ancestor."
    },
    {
      "index": "4",
      "start": "00:00:24,435",
      "end": "00:00:34,070",
      "text": "Some anatomists doubted the skull and jaw belonged together, but access was limited, prestige was heavy, and the specimen kept circulating as authority."
    },
    {
      "index": "5",
      "start": "00:00:34,771",
      "end": "00:00:36,033",
      "text": "The fraud was not perfect."
    },
    {
      "index": "6",
      "start": "00:00:36,774",
      "end": "00:00:37,435",
      "text": "It was welcome."
    },
    {
      "index": "7",
      "start": "00:00:38,417",
      "end": "00:00:42,323",
      "text": "By 1953, tests exposed the trick."
    },
    {
      "index": "8",
      "start": "00:00:42,302",
      "end": "00:00:44,189",
      "text": "The skull was recent human bone."
    },
    {
      "index": "9",
      "start": "00:00:44,993",
      "end": "00:00:46,537",
      "text": "The jaw was from an orangutan."
    },
    {
      "index": "10",
      "start": "00:00:47,200",
      "end": "00:00:48,505",
      "text": "The teeth had been filed."
    },
    {
      "index": "11",
      "start": "00:00:49,106",
      "end": "00:00:50,392",
      "text": "The bones had been stained."
    },
    {
      "index": "12",
      "start": "00:00:51,113",
      "end": "00:00:54,365",
      "text": "The hoax survived because it let the field feel correct."
    },
    {
      "index": "13",
      "start": "00:00:55,289",
      "end": "00:00:58,320",
      "text": "The mystery fades. The receipts remain."
    }
  ]
}
